: 1.7185185185185186, "no_speech_prob": 0.0006789634353481233}, {"id": 26, "seek": 10044, "start": 123.68, "end": 125.84, "text": " process is too rigorous.", "tokens": [51526, 1399, 307, 886, 29882, 13, 51634], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16591961600563743, "compression_ratio": 1.7185185185185186, "no_speech_prob": 0.0006789634353481233}, {"id": 27, "seek": 12584, "start": 125.84, "end": 131.16, "text": " For even a super minor change, you have to go through 17 levels of approval in triplicate.", "tokens": [50364, 1171, 754, 257, 1687, 6696, 1319, 11, 291, 362, 281, 352, 807, 3282, 4358, 295, 13317, 294, 1376, 4770, 473, 13, 50630], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.18639830292248336, "compression_ratio": 1.6586206896551725, "no_speech_prob": 0.06629905849695206}, {"id": 28, "seek": 12584, "start": 131.16, "end": 132.48000000000002, "text": " What happens then?", "tokens": [50630, 708, 2314, 550, 30, 50696], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.18639830292248336, "compression_ratio": 1.6586206896551725, "no_speech_prob": 0.06629905849695206}, {"id": 29, "seek": 12584, "start": 132.48000000000002, "end": 138.52, "text": " Well inevitably, if a change is too hard to make, if it's way too much paperwork to go through,", "tokens": [50696, 1042, 28171, 11, 498, 257, 1319, 307, 886, 1152, 281, 652, 11, 498, 309, 311, 636, 886, 709, 27953, 281, 352, 807, 11, 50998], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.18639830292248336, "compression_ratio": 1.6586206896551725, "no_speech_prob": 0.06629905849695206}, {"id": 30, "seek": 12584, "start": 138.52, "end": 143.32, "text": " people will find ways of avoiding the process and it'll also slow the organization down,", "tokens": [50998, 561, 486, 915, 2098, 295, 20220, 264, 1399, 293, 309, 603, 611, 2964, 264, 4475, 760, 11, 51238], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.18639830292248336, "compression_ratio": 1.6586206896551725, "no_speech_prob": 0.06629905849695206}, {"id": 31, "seek": 12584, "start": 143.32, "end": 147.6, "text": " make it so that it's too bureaucratic, too slow to get things done.", "tokens": [51238, 652, 309, 370, 300, 309, 311, 886, 26360, 25198, 11, 886, 2964, 281, 483, 721, 1096, 13, 51452], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.18639830292248336, "compression_ratio": 1.6586206896551725, "no_speech_prob": 0.06629905849695206}, {"id": 32, "seek": 12584, "start": 147.6, "end": 148.92000000000002, "text": " So that's kind of the challenges.", "tokens": [51452, 407, 300, 311, 733, 295, 264, 4759, 13, 51518], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.18639830292248336, "compression_ratio": 1.6586206896551725, "no_speech_prob": 0.06629905849695206}, {"id": 33, "seek": 12584, "start": 148.92000000000002, "end": 153.16, "text": " We want to find the happy middle in between them with our change management process.", "tokens": [51518, 492, 528, 281, 915, 264, 2055, 2808, 294, 1296, 552, 365, 527, 1319, 4592, 1399, 13, 51730], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.18639830292248336, "compression_ratio": 1.6586206896551725, "no_speech_prob": 0.06629905849695206}, {"id": 34, "seek": 15316, "start": 153.16, "end": 156.64, "text": " It needs to be flexible and it needs to be efficient.", "tokens": [50364, 467, 2203, 281, 312, 11358, 293, 309, 2203, 281, 312, 7148, 13, 50538], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14126164894404375, "compression_ratio": 1.786231884057971, "no_speech_prob": 0.00170498201623559}, {"id": 35, "seek": 15316, "start": 156.64, "end": 161.6, "text": " So now let's start to walk through the components of the change management process.", "tokens": [50538, 407, 586, 718, 311, 722, 281, 1792, 807, 264, 6677, 295, 264, 1319, 4592, 1399, 13, 50786], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14126164894404375, "compression_ratio": 1.786231884057971, "no_speech_prob": 0.00170498201623559}, {"id": 36, "seek": 15316, "start": 161.6, "end": 166.04, "text": " And the very first step is a change request comes in.", "tokens": [50786, 400, 264, 588, 700, 1823, 307, 257, 1319, 5308, 1487, 294, 13, 51008], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14126164894404375, "compression_ratio": 1.786231884057971, "no_speech_prob": 0.00170498201623559}, {"id": 37, "seek": 15316, "start": 166.04, "end": 167.48, "text": " Where can a change request come from?", "tokens": [51008, 2305, 393, 257, 1319, 5308, 808, 490, 30, 51080], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14126164894404375, "compression_ratio": 1.786231884057971, "no_speech_prob": 0.00170498201623559}, {"id": 38, "seek": 15316, "start": 167.48, "end": 171.8, "text": " Well, all sorts of different places, I might be to say, hey, we have to install a patch", "tokens": [51080, 1042, 11, 439, 7527, 295, 819, 3190, 11, 286, 1062, 312, 281, 584, 11, 4177, 11, 321, 362, 281, 3625, 257, 9972, 51296], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14126164894404375, "compression_ratio": 1.786231884057971, "no_speech_prob": 0.00170498201623559}, {"id": 39, "seek": 15316, "start": 171.8, "end": 175.16, "text": " on a system, make a configuration change to a system.", "tokens": [51296, 322, 257, 1185, 11, 652, 257, 11694, 1319, 281, 257, 1185, 13, 51464], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14126164894404375, "compression_ratio": 1.786231884057971, "no_speech_prob": 0.00170498201623559}, {"id": 40, "seek": 15316, "start": 175.16, "end": 180.0, "text": " We want to create a new system, we want to add some additional functionality, we want", "tokens": [51464, 492, 528, 281, 1884, 257, 777, 1185, 11, 321, 528, 281, 909, 512, 4497, 14980, 11, 321, 528, 51706], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14126164894404375, "compression_ratio": 1.786231884057971, "no_speech_prob": 0.00170498201623559}, {"id": 41, "seek": 15316, "start": 180.0, "end": 182.72, "text": " to do any of these sorts of things.", "tokens": [51706, 281, 360, 604, 295, 613, 7527, 295, 721, 13, 51842], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14126164894404375, "compression_ratio": 1.786231884057971, "no_speech_prob": 0.00170498201623559}, {"id": 42, "seek": 18272, "start": 182.72, "end": 186.96, "text": " So change requests can come from all over the organization.", "tokens": [50364, 407, 1319, 12475, 393, 808, 490, 439, 670, 264, 4475, 13, 50576], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14031257338196268, "compression_ratio": 1.7407407407407407, "no_speech_prob": 0.00029871921287849545}, {"id": 43, "seek": 18272, "start": 186.96, "end": 189.64, "text": " The next step is to do an impact analysis.", "tokens": [50576, 440, 958, 1823, 307, 281, 360, 364, 2712, 5215, 13, 50710], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14031257338196268, "compression_ratio": 1.7407407407407407, "no_speech_prob": 0.00029871921287849545}, {"id": 44, "seek": 18272, "start": 189.64, "end": 192.8, "text": " To figure out how big of a deal is this change?", "tokens": [50710, 1407, 2573, 484, 577, 955, 295, 257, 2028, 307, 341, 1319, 30, 50868], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14031257338196268, "compression_ratio": 1.7407407407407407, "no_speech_prob": 0.00029871921287849545}, {"id": 45, "seek": 18272, "start": 192.8, "end": 197.07999999999998, "text": " Is it a very minor change to a very low value system that can be done in just a few minutes", "tokens": [50868, 1119, 309, 257, 588, 6696, 1319, 281, 257, 588, 2295, 2158, 1185, 300, 393, 312, 1096, 294, 445, 257, 1326, 2077, 51082], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14031257338196268, "compression_ratio": 1.7407407407407407, "no_speech_prob": 0.00029871921287849545}, {"id": 46, "seek": 18272, "start": 197.07999999999998, "end": 198.68, "text": " and not affect anyone?", "tokens": [51082, 293, 406, 3345, 2878, 30, 51162], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14031257338196268, "compression_ratio": 1.7407407407407407, "no_speech_prob": 0.00029871921287849545}, {"id": 47, "seek": 18272, "start": 198.68, "end": 203.28, "text": " Or is this like a multi-million dollar project that's going to take months and it's going", "tokens": [51162, 1610, 307, 341, 411, 257, 4825, 12, 40388, 7241, 1716, 300, 311, 516, 281, 747, 2493, 293, 309, 311, 516, 51392], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14031257338196268, "compression_ratio": 1.7407407407407407, "no_speech_prob": 0.00029871921287849545}, {"id": 48, "seek": 18272, "start": 203.28, "end": 207.4, "text": " to cost millions of dollars and it can infect all sorts of different people?", "tokens": [51392, 281, 2063, 6803, 295, 3808, 293, 309, 393, 5888, 439, 7527, 295, 819, 561, 30, 51598], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14031257338196268, "compression_ratio": 1.7407407407407407, "no_speech_prob": 0.00029871921287849545}, {"id": 49, "seek": 18272, "start": 207.4, "end": 211.64, "text": " Or is this like an emergency patch that we need to do because there's a zero day out", "tokens": [51598, 1610, 307, 341, 411, 364, 7473, 9972, 300, 321, 643, 281, 360, 570, 456, 311, 257, 4018, 786, 484, 51810], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.14031257338196268, "compression_ratio": 1.7407407407407407, "no_speech_prob": 0.00029871921287849545}, {"id": 50, "seek": 21164, "start": 211.64, "end": 215.64, "text": " there and we have to patch these systems yesterday?", "tokens": [50364, 456, 293, 321, 362, 281, 9972, 613, 3652, 5186, 30, 50564], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12675764754011826, "compression_ratio": 1.7653846153846153, "no_speech_prob": 0.01079645473510027}, {"id": 51, "seek": 21164, "start": 215.64, "end": 220.04, "text": " The impact analysis will identify what type of change it is, which will then drive the", "tokens": [50564, 440, 2712, 5215, 486, 5876, 437, 2010, 295, 1319, 309, 307, 11, 597, 486, 550, 3332, 264, 50784], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12675764754011826, "compression_ratio": 1.7653846153846153, "no_speech_prob": 0.01079645473510027}, {"id": 52, "seek": 21164, "start": 220.04, "end": 221.64, "text": " rest of the process.", "tokens": [50784, 1472, 295, 264, 1399, 13, 50864], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12675764754011826, "compression_ratio": 1.7653846153846153, "no_speech_prob": 0.01079645473510027}, {"id": 53, "seek": 21164, "start": 221.64, "end": 225.76, "text": " For very expensive, very big changes that affect a lot of people, you probably need to go", "tokens": [50864, 1171, 588, 5124, 11, 588, 955, 2962, 300, 3345, 257, 688, 295, 561, 11, 291, 1391, 643, 281, 352, 51070], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12675764754011826, "compression_ratio": 1.7653846153846153, "no_speech_prob": 0.01079645473510027}, {"id": 54, "seek": 21164, "start": 225.76, "end": 228.16, "text": " through a lot of levels of approval.", "tokens": [51070, 807, 257, 688, 295, 4358, 295, 13317, 13, 51190], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12675764754011826, "compression_ratio": 1.7653846153846153, "no_speech_prob": 0.01079645473510027}, {"id": 55, "seek": 21164, "start": 228.16, "end": 232.51999999999998, "text": " For emergency changes, you might skip a lot of those approvals to very quickly implement", "tokens": [51190, 1171, 7473, 2962, 11, 291, 1062, 10023, 257, 688, 295, 729, 2075, 19778, 281, 588, 2661, 4445, 51408], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12675764754011826, "compression_ratio": 1.7653846153846153, "no_speech_prob": 0.01079645473510027}, {"id": 56, "seek": 21164, "start": 232.51999999999998, "end": 234.92, "text": " the change.", "tokens": [51408, 264, 1319, 13, 51528], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12675764754011826, "compression_ratio": 1.7653846153846153, "no_speech_prob": 0.01079645473510027}, {"id": 57, "seek": 21164, "start": 234.92, "end": 238.83999999999997, "text": " So the next step of the change management process is the approval step.", "tokens": [51528, 407, 264, 958, 1823, 295, 264, 1319, 4592, 1399, 307, 264, 13317, 1823, 13, 51724], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.12675764754011826, "compression_ratio": 1.7653846153846153, "no_speech_prob": 0.01079645473510027}, {"id": 58, "seek": 23884, "start": 238.84, "end": 242.04, "text": " This is where someone actually needs to approve the change.", "tokens": [50364, 639, 307, 689, 1580, 767, 2203, 281, 18827, 264, 1319, 13, 50524], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1365883409484359, "compression_ratio": 1.6996466431095407, "no_speech_prob": 0.047451671212911606}, {"id": 59, "seek": 23884, "start": 242.04, "end": 245.48000000000002, "text": " And this is probably where you've heard of terms like cabs or e-cabs.", "tokens": [50524, 400, 341, 307, 1391, 689, 291, 600, 2198, 295, 2115, 411, 5487, 82, 420, 308, 12, 66, 17243, 13, 50696], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1365883409484359, "compression_ratio": 1.6996466431095407, "no_speech_prob": 0.047451671212911606}, {"id": 60, "seek": 23884, "start": 245.48000000000002, "end": 250.56, "text": " A cab is a change advisory board made up of stakeholders from all across the organization", "tokens": [50696, 316, 5487, 307, 257, 1319, 26289, 3150, 1027, 493, 295, 17779, 490, 439, 2108, 264, 4475, 50950], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1365883409484359, "compression_ratio": 1.6996466431095407, "no_speech_prob": 0.047451671212911606}, {"id": 61, "seek": 23884, "start": 250.56, "end": 255.56, "text": " that can provide input on whether or not this change makes sense, if it's cost effective,", "tokens": [50950, 300, 393, 2893, 4846, 322, 1968, 420, 406, 341, 1319, 1669, 2020, 11, 498, 309, 311, 2063, 4942, 11, 51200], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1365883409484359, "compression_ratio": 1.6996466431095407, "no_speech_prob": 0.047451671212911606}, {"id": 62, "seek": 23884, "start": 255.56, "end": 260.8, "text": " how to do it in an efficient way, how to minimize impact, all these sorts of things.", "tokens": [51200, 577, 281, 360, 309, 294, 364, 7148, 636, 11, 577, 281, 17522, 2712, 11, 439, 613, 7527, 295, 721, 13, 51462], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1365883409484359, "compression_ratio": 1.6996466431095407, "no_speech_prob": 0.047451671212911606}, {"id": 63, "seek": 23884, "start": 260.8, "end": 266.92, "text": " And if it's a really big change, you might even escalate up to e-cap, executive change", "tokens": [51462, 400, 498, 309, 311, 257, 534, 955, 1319, 11, 291, 1062, 754, 17871, 473, 493, 281, 308, 12, 9485, 11, 10140, 1319, 51768], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.1365883409484359, "compression_ratio": 1.6996466431095407, "no_speech_prob": 0.047451671212911606}, {"id": 64, "seek": 26692, "start": 266.96000000000004, "end": 269.64000000000004, "text": " advisory boards.", "tokens": [50366, 26289, 13293, 13, 50500], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.19531003360090585, "compression_ratio": 1.75, "no_speech_prob": 0.004010468255728483}, {"id": 65, "seek": 26692, "start": 269.64000000000004, "end": 271.56, "text": " The next step is build and test.", "tokens": [50500, 440, 958, 1823, 307, 1322, 293, 1500, 13, 50596], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.19531003360090585, "compression_ratio": 1.75, "no_speech_prob": 0.004010468255728483}, {"id": 66, "seek": 26692, "start": 271.56, "end": 275.96000000000004, "text": " So actually start to create whatever the change is, test to make sure the change is going", "tokens": [50596, 407, 767, 722, 281, 1884, 2035, 264, 1319, 307, 11, 1500, 281, 652, 988, 264, 1319, 307, 516, 50816], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.19531003360090585, "compression_ratio": 1.75, "no_speech_prob": 0.004010468255728483}, {"id": 67, "seek": 26692, "start": 275.96000000000004, "end": 279.0, "text": " to work properly, start to create back-out plans.", "tokens": [50816, 281, 589, 6108, 11, 722, 281, 1884, 646, 12, 346, 5482, 13, 50968], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.19531003360090585, "compression_ratio": 1.75, "no_speech_prob": 0.004010468255728483}, {"id": 68, "seek": 26692, "start": 279.0, "end": 284.24, "text": " So if the change doesn't go well, you can get back to it in our previous state.", "tokens": [50968, 407, 498, 264, 1319, 1177, 380, 352, 731, 11, 291, 393, 483, 646, 281, 309, 294, 527, 3894, 1785, 13, 51230], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.19531003360090585, "compression_ratio": 1.75, "no_speech_prob": 0.004010468255728483}, {"id": 69, "seek": 26692, "start": 284.24, "end": 286.20000000000005, "text": " Next is notification.", "tokens": [51230, 3087, 307, 11554, 13, 51328], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.19531003360090585, "compression_ratio": 1.75, "no_speech_prob": 0.004010468255728483}, {"id": 70, "seek": 26692, "start": 286.20000000000005, "end": 291.08000000000004, "text": " Notification is where you notify all the relevant stakeholders that the change is about", "tokens": [51328, 1726, 3774, 307, 689, 291, 36560, 439, 264, 7340, 17779, 300, 264, 1319, 307, 466, 51572], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.19531003360090585, "compression_ratio": 1.75, "no_speech_prob": 0.004010468255728483}, {"id": 71, "seek": 26692, "start": 291.08000000000004, "end": 292.08000000000004, "text": " to occur.", "tokens": [51572, 281, 5160, 13, 51622], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.19531003360090585, "compression_ratio": 1.75, "no_speech_prob": 0.004010468255728483}, {"id": 72, "seek": 26692, "start": 292.08000000000004, "end": 295.56, "text": " That might be consumers, it might be business owners, management.", "tokens": [51622, 663, 1062, 312, 11883, 11, 309, 1062, 312, 1606, 7710, 11, 4592, 13, 51796], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.19531003360090585, "compression_ratio": 1.75, "no_speech_prob": 0.004010468255728483}, {"id": 73, "seek": 29556, "start": 296.12, "end": 300.88, "text": " Whoever needs to know, whoever is a relevant stakeholder, you need to notify them because", "tokens": [50392, 24743, 2203, 281, 458, 11, 11387, 307, 257, 7340, 43406, 11, 291, 643, 281, 36560, 552, 570, 50630], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16485080384371573, "compression_ratio": 1.841726618705036, "no_speech_prob": 0.001981796231120825}, {"id": 74, "seek": 29556, "start": 300.88, "end": 305.72, "text": " you're about to actually implement the change.", "tokens": [50630, 291, 434, 466, 281, 767, 4445, 264, 1319, 13, 50872], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16485080384371573, "compression_ratio": 1.841726618705036, "no_speech_prob": 0.001981796231120825}, {"id": 75, "seek": 29556, "start": 305.72, "end": 309.08, "text": " The next step after implementation is validation.", "tokens": [50872, 440, 958, 1823, 934, 11420, 307, 24071, 13, 51040], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16485080384371573, "compression_ratio": 1.841726618705036, "no_speech_prob": 0.001981796231120825}, {"id": 76, "seek": 29556, "start": 309.08, "end": 312.64, "text": " And this is where you check to make sure that, okay, this change was supposed to provide", "tokens": [51040, 400, 341, 307, 689, 291, 1520, 281, 652, 988, 300, 11, 1392, 11, 341, 1319, 390, 3442, 281, 2893, 51218], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16485080384371573, "compression_ratio": 1.841726618705036, "no_speech_prob": 0.001981796231120825}, {"id": 77, "seek": 29556, "start": 312.64, "end": 315.8, "text": " this new functionality or patch this system.", "tokens": [51218, 341, 777, 14980, 420, 9972, 341, 1185, 13, 51376], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16485080384371573, "compression_ratio": 1.841726618705036, "no_speech_prob": 0.001981796231120825}, {"id": 78, "seek": 29556, "start": 315.8, "end": 319.56, "text": " So the validation step is where you make sure that whatever the change was has actually", "tokens": [51376, 407, 264, 24071, 1823, 307, 689, 291, 652, 988, 300, 2035, 264, 1319, 390, 575, 767, 51564], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16485080384371573, "compression_ratio": 1.841726618705036, "no_speech_prob": 0.001981796231120825}, {"id": 79, "seek": 29556, "start": 319.56, "end": 321.36, "text": " occurred correctly.", "tokens": [51564, 11068, 8944, 13, 51654], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16485080384371573, "compression_ratio": 1.841726618705036, "no_speech_prob": 0.001981796231120825}, {"id": 80, "seek": 29556, "start": 321.36, "end": 325.36, "text": " And this is also where you include that testing that we've talked about, regression", "tokens": [51654, 400, 341, 307, 611, 689, 291, 4090, 300, 4997, 300, 321, 600, 2825, 466, 11, 24590, 51854], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.16485080384371573, "compression_ratio": 1.841726618705036, "no_speech_prob": 0.001981796231120825}, {"id": 81, "seek": 32536, "start": 325.36, "end": 328.84000000000003, "text": " testing, progression testing, of course, is where you go back and make sure you haven't", "tokens": [50364, 4997, 11, 18733, 4997, 11, 295, 1164, 11, 307, 689, 291, 352, 646, 293, 652, 988, 291, 2378, 380, 50538], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.17786436421530588, "compression_ratio": 1.7575757575757576, "no_speech_prob": 0.0008184917969629169}, {"id": 82, "seek": 32536, "start": 328.84000000000003, "end": 331.56, "text": " broken any existing functionality.", "tokens": [50538, 5463, 604, 6741, 14980, 13, 50674], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.17786436421530588, "compression_ratio": 1.7575757575757576, "no_speech_prob": 0.0008184917969629169}, {"id": 83, "seek": 32536, "start": 331.56, "end": 334.64, "text": " So all this falls under validation.", "tokens": [50674, 407, 439, 341, 8804, 833, 24071, 13, 50828], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.17786436421530588, "compression_ratio": 1.7575757575757576, "no_speech_prob": 0.0008184917969629169}, {"id": 84, "seek": 32536, "start": 334.64, "end": 338.64, "text": " And then the final step is updating your versioning, your baselines.", "tokens": [50828, 400, 550, 264, 2572, 1823, 307, 25113, 428, 3037, 278, 11, 428, 987, 9173, 13, 51028], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.17786436421530588, "compression_ratio": 1.7575757575757576, "no_speech_prob": 0.0008184917969629169}, {"id": 85, "seek": 32536, "start": 338.64, "end": 343.56, "text": " So we've talked about baselines, a baseline is the standard configuration for a system", "tokens": [51028, 407, 321, 600, 2825, 466, 987, 9173, 11, 257, 20518, 307, 264, 3832, 11694, 337, 257, 1185, 51274], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.17786436421530588, "compression_ratio": 1.7575757575757576, "no_speech_prob": 0.0008184917969629169}, {"id": 86, "seek": 32536, "start": 343.56, "end": 347.48, "text": " of all the controls or all the configuration that should be in place.", "tokens": [51274, 295, 439, 264, 9003, 420, 439, 264, 11694, 300, 820, 312, 294, 1081, 13, 51470], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.17786436421530588, "compression_ratio": 1.7575757575757576, "no_speech_prob": 0.0008184917969629169}, {"id": 87, "seek": 32536, "start": 347.48, "end": 352.12, "text": " If you've made a change to a system, you need to update that system's baseline.", "tokens": [51470, 759, 291, 600, 1027, 257, 1319, 281, 257, 1185, 11, 291, 643, 281, 5623, 300, 1185, 311, 20518, 13, 51702], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.17786436421530588, "compression_ratio": 1.7575757575757576, "no_speech_prob": 0.0008184917969629169}, {"id": 88, "seek": 35212, "start": 352.12, "end": 356.4, "text": " You might also, this may also trigger you to go and update for certain plans like say", "tokens": [50364, 509, 1062, 611, 11, 341, 815, 611, 7875, 291, 281, 352, 293, 5623, 337, 1629, 5482, 411, 584, 50578], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.18504626795930681, "compression_ratio": 1.7171314741035857, "no_speech_prob": 0.006100207567214966}, {"id": 89, "seek": 35212, "start": 356.4, "end": 361.44, "text": " the DRP plan because your DRP plan is meant to recover a system.", "tokens": [50578, 264, 12118, 47, 1393, 570, 428, 12118, 47, 1393, 307, 4140, 281, 8114, 257, 1185, 13, 50830], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.18504626795930681, "compression_ratio": 1.7171314741035857, "no_speech_prob": 0.006100207567214966}, {"id": 90, "seek": 35212, "start": 361.44, "end": 365.84000000000003, "text": " And it obviously needs to recover the system to wherever it was right before it failed,", "tokens": [50830, 400, 309, 2745, 2203, 281, 8114, 264, 1185, 281, 8660, 309, 390, 558, 949, 309, 7612, 11, 51050], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.18504626795930681, "compression_ratio": 1.7171314741035857, "no_speech_prob": 0.006100207567214966}, {"id": 91, "seek": 35212, "start": 365.84000000000003, "end": 371.44, "text": " which means any changes you've made to the system might require an update to the DRP plan.", "tokens": [51050, 597, 1355, 604, 2962, 291, 600, 1027, 281, 264, 1185, 1062, 3651, 364, 5623, 281, 264, 12118, 47, 1393, 13, 51330], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.18504626795930681, "compression_ratio": 1.7171314741035857, "no_speech_prob": 0.006100207567214966}, {"id": 92, "seek": 35212, "start": 371.44, "end": 375.92, "text": " So there's a bunch of updating of documents that might need to occur at the end of change", "tokens": [51330, 407, 456, 311, 257, 3840, 295, 25113, 295, 8512, 300, 1062, 643, 281, 5160, 412, 264, 917, 295, 1319, 51554], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.18504626795930681, "compression_ratio": 1.7171314741035857, "no_speech_prob": 0.006100207567214966}, {"id": 93, "seek": 35212, "start": 375.92, "end": 377.6, "text": " management.", "tokens": [51554, 4592, 13, 51638], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.18504626795930681, "compression_ratio": 1.7171314741035857, "no_speech_prob": 0.006100207567214966}, {"id": 94, "seek": 37760, "start": 378.56, "end": 383.04, "text": " And there's one final piece that's not mentioned here, but it's included throughout all of these steps.", "tokens": [50412, 400, 456, 311, 472, 2572, 2522, 300, 311, 406, 2835, 510, 11, 457, 309, 311, 5556, 3710, 439, 295, 613, 4439, 13, 50636], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15845081418059592, "compression_ratio": 1.8409893992932862, "no_speech_prob": 0.0247146338224411}, {"id": 95, "seek": 37760, "start": 383.04, "end": 385.12, "text": " And that is documentation.", "tokens": [50636, 400, 300, 307, 14333, 13, 50740], "temperature": 0.0, "avg_logprob": -0.15845081418059592, "compressio